quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,"About what are they asking one another?"
  78,2,"Is it about the awesome tiding"
  78,3,"that they are in utter disagreement?",footnotes:182521:1
  78,4,"No indeed; soon will they come to know;",footnotes:182522:1|182523:2
  78,5,"again, no indeed; soon will they come to know."
  78,6,"Have We not spread the earth like a bed,",footnotes:182524:1
  78,7,"and fixed the mountains like pegs,",footnotes:182525:1
  78,8,"and created you in pairs (as men and women),",footnotes:182526:1
  78,9,"and made your sleep a means of repose,",footnotes:182527:1
  78,10,"and made the night a covering,"
  78,11,"and made the day to seek livelihood,",footnotes:182528:1
  78,12,"and built above you seven strong firmaments,",footnotes:182529:1
  78,13,"and placed therein a hot, shining lamp,",footnotes:182530:1
  78,14,"and sent down abundant water from the clouds"
  78,15,"so that We may thereby bring forth grain and vegetation,"
  78,16,"and gardens dense with foliage?",footnotes:182531:1
  78,17,"Surely the Day of Judgement has an appointed time;"
  78,18,"the Day when the Trumpet shall be blown, and you will come forth in multitudes;",footnotes:182532:1
  78,19,"and when the sky shall be opened up and will become all doors;"
  78,20,"and the mountains will be set in motion and become a mirage.",footnotes:182533:1
  78,21,"Surely the Hell is an ambush,",footnotes:182534:1
  78,22,"a resort for the rebellious;"
  78,23,"therein they shall abide for ages,",footnotes:182535:1
  78,24,"they shall taste in it no coolness, nor any pleasant drink"
  78,25,"save boiling water and wash of the wounds;",footnotes:182536:1
  78,26,"a befitting recompense for their deeds."
  78,27,"For indeed they did not look forward to any reckoning,"
  78,28,"and roundly denied Our Signs as false.",footnotes:182537:1
  78,29,"And everything have We recorded in a Book.",footnotes:182538:1
  78,30,"So taste (the fruit of your deeds). We shall only increase your torment."
  78,31,"Surely the state of triumph awaits the God-fearing:",footnotes:182539:1
  78,32,"gardens and vineyards,"
  78,33,"and youthful maidens of like age,",footnotes:182540:1
  78,34,"and an overflowing cup."
  78,35,"Therein they shall hear no idle talk, nor any falsehood;",footnotes:182541:1
  78,36,"a recompense from your Lord and an ample reward",footnotes:182542:1
  78,37,"from the Lord of the heavens and the earth and of that which is between them; the Most Merciful Lord before Whom none dare utter a word.",footnotes:182543:1
  78,38,"The Day when the Spirit and the angels are ranged row on row. None shall speak save he whom the Merciful Lord will permit; and he too will speak what is right.",footnotes:182544:1|182545:2
  78,39,"That Day is sure to come. So let him who will seek a resort with his Lord."
  78,40,"Lo! We warn you of a chastisement near at hand; the Day when a man will look on what his own hands have sent forth, and the unbelievers shall say: “Oh would that I were utter dust.”",footnotes:182546:1|182547:2
